    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nI wonder if would be helpful to create the mentioned modules to group some functions in a similar way to those in the `vim.treesitter` module\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nFor example, a `vim.fmt.{format}` or `vim.format.{format}` like\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nvim.fmt.base64.{method}\r\nvim.fmt.json.{method}\r\nvim.fmt.text.{method}\r\nvim.fmt.mpack.{method}\r\n```\r\n\r\nA `vim.types.{type}` like\r\n\r\n```lua      \r\nvim.types.tbl.{method}  -- for all vim.tbl_* methods\r\nvim.types.list.{method} -- for all vim.list_* methods\r\nvim.types.str.{method}  -- for all vim.str_* methods\r\n```",
    "closed_at": "2024-05-21T13:26:44Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This is deliberate: We prefer a \"flat\" hierarchy; that simplifies a few things (for example, you don't have to export local functions across modules).",
